        <p><strong>Where Jasper wins:</strong> if you have a 5+ person marketing team and brand voice consistency matters more than cost. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if your goal is published articles, not a content workflow. Pick by the job, not the brand.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Jasper AI?</h2>
        <p>Jasper AI is an enterprise AI writing platform founded in 2021 by Dave Rogenmoser. Originally branded as Jarvis (then renamed to avoid the Marvel trademark), Jasper rode the GPT-3 wave to a $1.5B valuation in late 2022. Then ChatGPT launched, commoditized basic AI writing overnight, and Jasper pivoted hard into enterprise — brand voice, team workflows, governance, polish.</p>

        <p>The core suite does five things:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Long-form editor</strong> — Google Docs-style canvas with inline AI commands</li>
          <li><strong>Brand voice training</strong> — upload writing samples, Jasper learns your style</li>
          <li><strong>Templates</strong> — 50+ structured generators (blog intros, ads, product copy)</li>
          <li><strong>Image generation</strong> — Jasper Art for blog headers and social</li>
          <li><strong>Team collaboration</strong> — roles, workflows, review queues, audit logs</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Jasper is <em>not</em>: an SEO scoring tool, a publishing platform, or a CMS. It writes content. Optimization and publishing are separate workflows.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>Jasper raised $125M Series A at a $1.5B valuation in October 2022 from Insight Partners and Coatue. Post-ChatGPT, the company has reportedly cut headcount and refocused on enterprise. Revenue is estimated at $80–120M ARR. CEO Dave Rogenmoser remains in charge. The pivot from broad consumer to enterprise has narrowed the customer base but raised average contract value.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">Jasper AI features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is enterprise-grade. Here's what actually matters in daily use.</p>

        <h3>1. Long-form editor</h3>
        <p>The canvas where most of the work happens. Google Docs-style interface with inline AI commands (Cmd+J), templates, and SEO scoring (when Surfer is connected). Genuinely the smoothest long-form AI writing experience on the market.</p>

        <h3>2. Brand voice training</h3>
        <p>Upload 30+ writing samples and Jasper learns your tone, vocabulary, formality, and structural preferences. Every subsequent generation respects the trained voice. The single feature that justifies the price premium for enterprise teams.</p>

        <h3>3. Templates (50+)</h3>
        <p>Structured generators for blog intros, paragraph rewrites, ad copy, product descriptions, AIDA frameworks, PAS frameworks, video scripts, email sequences, and more. Each template prompts you for inputs and returns formatted output. Most useful for short-form work.</p>

        <h3>4. Jasper Art (image generation)</h3>
        <p>Bundled image generation for blog headers, social posts, and concept art. Output quality is competent — about on par with mid-tier Stable Diffusion. Saves you from a separate Midjourney subscription if image needs are modest.</p>

        <h3>5. Team workflows (Business)</h3>
        <p>Role-based access, review queues, brand voice governance, audit logs, SSO, and analytics. Genuinely useful for teams of 5+ where brand consistency matters across multiple writers.</p>

        <h3>6. Surfer SEO integration</h3>
        <p>Native integration with Surfer SEO. Write inside Jasper, see real-time SEO scores from Surfer in the sidebar. Requires a separate Surfer subscription ($99+/mo). This is the standard SEO content workflow for Jasper users.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">Jasper AI pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>Jasper publishes pricing. Here are the live numbers — plus the add-ons most users don't budget for.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
